        <div class="bk-meta en">History · 2024</div><div class="bk-meta zh" style="display:none">历史 · 2025</div>
        <div class="bk-title en">Stories of the Ming Dynasty — Dangnian Mingyue</div><div class="bk-title zh" style="display:none">《明朝那些事儿》— 当年明月</div>
        <div class="bk-author en">Dangnian Mingyue, 2006–2009</div><div class="bk-author zh" style="display:none">当年明月，2006–2009</div>
        <div class="bk-rating">★★★★★</div>
        <p class="bk-notes en">The words of "Dangnian Mingyue" have, to some extent, influenced my writing style. As a result, in my current writings, serious narratives often have to be interspersed with a touch of humor, and even occasionally reveal a hint of nonsensical elements. However, it is precisely under this seemingly relaxed and even slightly casual writing style that I unexpectedly touched upon a long-lost idealistic light. From Wang Yangming's philosophy of the mind and the unity of knowledge and action, to Hai Rui's straightness and integrity, and then to Zhang Juzheng's weighing and reform, these figures have not been buried by the dust of history. Instead, they have once again radiated a certain almost stubborn belief and light between the lines.</p>
        <p class="bk-notes zh" style="display:none">当年明月的文字在某种程度上影响了我的文风，以至于我现在的文字里，往往严肃的叙述偏要夹杂几分诙谐，甚至偶尔流露出一点无厘头。然而正是在这种看似轻松甚至略显随意的笔触之下，我却意外地触碰到一种久违的理想主义光芒，从王阳明的心学与知行合一，到海瑞的刚直与清廉，再到张居正的权衡与改革，这些人物并未被历史的尘埃掩埋，反而在字里行间重新焕发出某种近乎执拗的信念与光亮。</p>
